                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2696</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-22T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram August 21, 4 p.m. The President informs me that eighteen provinces
                    nave accepted the plan of a provisional National Council of five members from
                    each province which is to complete the Constitution and parliamentary election
                    law. Kwangtung, Kwangsi, Yunnan, have not yet agreed but he hopes to persuade
                    them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
